bccpir: Concealed carry permits issued to residents? (2 if permit not needed for CC, 1 if yes, 0 if no)
bccpin: Concealed carry permits issued to nonresidents? (2 if permit not needed for CC, 1 if yes,.5 if yes for property owners/employed in state/may issue, 0 if no)
bsi: Concealed carry permits are shall-issue? (2 if permit not needed, 1 if yes, 0.5 if theoretically yes but broad exceptions exist or theoretically may issue but effectively more like shall issue, 0 if no)
Bplaces: Is loaded handgun carry permitted in bars, banks, casinos, hospitals, places of worship, public demonstrations, parks, and athletic events? (1=yes, 0=no)
Bopen: Open carry of loaded handgun (permitted without permit=2, permitted with permit=1, not generally permitted=0)
Bjourn: Carry in motor vehicles (peaceable journey) (3=no restrictions even if concealed, 2= either “plain view” or “concealed” restrictions, 1=only with concealed carry permit (unless in locked container or glove box), 0.5=permitted with CC permit/license but only if in plain view, 0=not permitted unless locked in container)
Bpreoc: State preemption of local open carry ordinances? (1=yes, 0.5=limited/special legislation for particular localities, 0=no)
Bprecc: State preemption of local concealed carry ordinances? (1=yes, 0.5=limited/special legislation for particular localities, 0=no)
Bgunban: Local gun ban in place? (1=sale & possession, 0.5=sale only, 0=none)
Bnpg: Non powder guns' use or possession regulated? (1=yes, 0.5=locally, 0=no or just deals with young minors)
Bminage: Stricter minimum age to purchase or possess firearms than federal standard? (1=yes, 0=no)
Bwait: Waiting period on firearms purchases? (1=all firearms, 0.5=some firearms, 0=no)
Bdealer: Licensing or regulation of gun dealers? (1=yes, 0.5=locally or only warning to purchasers, 0=no)
bstheft: Gun dealer regulation: mandatory theft reporting of all firearms (1=yes, 0=no)
botheft: Owners required to report lost or stolen guns? (1=yes, 0=no)
Bpriv: Background checks required at private sales or gun shows? (1=yes, 0.5=locally or some firearms, 0=no)
Blicens: Licensing or permitting of gun owners or purchasers? (1=all guns, 0.5=handguns only, 0=no; multiplied by 0.5 if locally only)
Bregis: Registration of firearms? (1=all firearms, 0.5=some firearms, 0=no – multiplied by 0.5 if locally only)
Bdesign: Design safety standards for handguns ("Saturday night special" ban)? (1=yes, 0=no)
Blocks: Built-in locking devices required? (2=yes and must be stored in a locked container or with lock in place, 1=yes with sale, 0=no)
Bchild: Child access prevention laws? (3=criminal liability if child may gain access, 2=criminal liability if child actually gains access, 1=criminal liability if access provided knowingly, intentionally, or recklessly/child must use gun, 0=none, multiplied by 0.5 if local only, multiplied by 0.5 if gun must be loaded and/or a handgun for liability to attach)
baurnh: Authorized user requirement for new handguns, aka smartguns? (1=yes, 0=no)
bdtr: Law specifying no duty to retreat before using deadly force? (1=yes, applying everywhere, 0.75 home & vehicle, 0.5=only in home (aka castle doctrine), 0=none)
Bretent: Retention of sales records? (1=kept by state, 0.5=kept by seller, 0=no requirement – multiplied by 0.5 if locally only)
Bconst: State constitution contains individual right to keep and bear arms? (1=yes, 0=no)
bmg: Machine Guns (1 if not prohibited by state law; .5 if not prohibited but regulated at state-local level OR not prohibited in law but virtually prohibited in practice; 0 if prohibited in state law)
bss: Sound Suppressor (Silencers) (1 if not prohibited by state law; .5 if not prohibited but regulated at state-local level OR not prohibited in law but virtually prohibited in practice; 0 if prohibited in state law)
bsbr: SBR (Short Barreled Rifle) (1 if not prohibited by state law; .5 if not prohibited but regulated at state-local level OR not prohibited in law but virtually prohibited in practice; 0 if prohibited in state law)
bsbs: SBS (Short Barreled Shotgun) (1 if not prohibited by state law; .5 if not prohibited but regulated at state-local level OR not prohibited in law but virtually prohibited in practice; 0 if prohibited in state law)
